gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Kings 143, Wizards 131
gameRecap.excerpt: The Kings defeated the Wizards, 143-131. Domantas Sabonis led the way with his third triple-double of the season, 35th of his career (28 points, 13 rebounds, 12 assists), while DeAaron Fox (30 points, five rebounds, six assists, three steals) and Keegan Murray (25 points, five rebounds, four assists, four 3PM) combine for 55 in the victory.  Jordan Poole tallied 28 points and eight 3PM for the Wizards in the losing effort.  The Kings improve to 16-9 on the season, while the Wizards fall to 4-22.
